                <h2>General Information</h2>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What is the Indian Cultural Management System?</h3>
                    <p>The Indian Cultural Management System is a platform designed to preserve, promote, and manage various aspects of Indian culture, including festivals, traditions, art, music, dance, literature, and heritage sites.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What features does the Indian Cultural Management System offer?</h3>
                    <p>The Indian Cultural Management System provides features such as event management for festivals, cultural heritage preservation, online galleries for art and artifacts, digital libraries for literature, and educational resources for Indian culture.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>How can I use the Indian Cultural Management System?</h3>
                    <p>The Indian Cultural Management System is accessible through its website and mobile applications. Users can explore various cultural events, exhibitions, and educational resources, as well as participate in cultural activities and contribute to the preservation of Indian heritage.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Is the Indian Cultural Management System free to use?</h3>
                    <p>Yes, the Indian Cultural Management System is free to use for both individual users and organizations. However, certain premium features may require a subscription or payment.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>How can I contribute to the Indian Cultural Management System?</h3>
                    <p>Users can contribute to the Indian Cultural Management System by submitting their cultural events, artworks, literature, and other cultural artifacts. They can also participate in cultural discussions, forums, and educational programs.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Is the Indian Cultural Management System available in multiple languages?</h3>
                    <p>Yes, the Indian Cultural Management System is available in multiple languages to cater to users from diverse linguistic backgrounds across India and around the world.</p>
                </div>
